  "instructions": [
    "In a large clay pot or Dutch oven, heat the olive oil over medium heat.",
    "Add the onion and garlic and cook until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the smoked lamb shoulder and cook for 2 minutes on each side, or until browned.",
    "Add the diced tomatoes, palm sugar, smoked paprika, salt, black pepper, preserved lemon, red pepper flakes, and grape molasses. Stir to combine.",
    "Add the water to the pot and bring to a boil.",
    "Transfer the pot to the refrigerator and let it smoke-chill for at least 2 hours.",
    "Preheat the grill or oven to 400°F (200°C).",
    "Remove the pot from the refrigerator and let it come to room temperature.",
    "Grill or bake the Tagine for 30 minutes, or until the meat is tender and the flavors have melded together.",
    "Garnish with cilantro and serve with smoked fish (if using)."
